Add Title/Logo/Refresh Date 14


I will be using the default theme colors for this project, but you can choose any theme you like just make sure it doesn't uses Green, Red, or Yellow, those colors are reserved for other functionalities. 

Steps: Colaberry Logo

  1. In Power BI Desktop, select Insert tab from the ribbon, then select Image
  2. Browser the data file we downloaded earlier and select the 'Logo' image then,
  3. click Open

  4. Format: Logo formatting 

    1. Select the Logo and in in the Format pane change the following:
    2. Style = Normal,
    3. Size: Height = 40, Width = 116, 
    4. Position: Horizontal = 15, Vert = 2
    5. Title: title and Header icons = off
    6. Effects: Background, Visual border, Shadow = off

    Step: Title

    1. Select Insert tab from the ribbon, then select 'Text box' 
    2. Type in "U.S POLICE SHOOTING" 

    3. Format.

      1. Font = Segoe UI, font-size = 16, style = Bold, align = Center
      2. Height = 40, width = 338, 
      3. position: Horizontal = 471, Vert = 4

      Step: Last Refreshed On

      1. In Fields pane expand the 'Last Refreshed' table and drag into the canvas 

      2. Format: Last Refreshed On 

        1. In the Visualizations pane, click on "Format your visual" 
        2. Under Visual expand Callout value and change the following,
        3. Callout Value: Fond = DIN, Size = 14, Color = Black, 
        4. Category label: off 
        5. Under General, 
        6. Properties, expand Size change Height = 40, Width = 184
        7. Expand Position change Horizontal = 196 and Vertical = 0
        8. Turn Title off
